The paper deals with optimization problems over massive data sets, which is a common theme in the sub-fields of distributed systems (cs.DS) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of composable core-sets is a technique that is often employed in distributed computing (cs.DC) and optimization (cs.AI) literature. The paper also discusses the use of MapReduce-based algorithms, which is a common tool in distributed computing (cs.DC) and information theory (cs.IT).
